    "During the model evaluation process, two different thresholds were used as cut-off values to classify into positive and negative classes for the predicted scores.",
    "The threshold with a cut-off value of 25 was used based on previous work and recommendations from the literature based on a German sample 43, while our ROC curve research revealed that the threshold of 18 was the most efficient.",
    "A potential explanation for such results is given in the discussion.",
    "Presented values include separate classification metrics in classifying positive and negative cases, as well as weighted values as aggregate measures including both classes.",
